aft-panthers-begin-matt-rhule-era-with-a-new-quarterback-patriots-get-a-nice-surprise/ |website=CBS Sports |accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Greenberg |first1=Ethan |title=NFL Draft Profile: LSU QB Joe Burrow |url=https://www.newyorkjets.com/news/nfl-draft-profile-lsu-qb-joe-burrow |website=New York Jets |accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref> Burrow was one of 58 players invited to the draft, which is to be held virtually due to [[social distancing]] regulations arising from the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shook |first1=Nick |title=Joe Burrow, Chase Young to participate in NFL draft |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001108846/article/joe-burrow-chase-young-to-participate-in-nfl-draft |website=NFL.com |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n*[http://www.lsusports.net/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5200&ATCLID=211716545 LSU Tigers bio]\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Joe Burrow|list=\n{{LSU Tigers quarterback navbox}}\n{{2019 LSU Tigers football navbox}}\n{{Heisman Trophy}}\n{{Maxwell Award}}\n{{Walter Camp Award}}\n{{AP College Football Player of the Year}}\n{{Sporting News College Football Player of the Year}}\n{{2019 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{Davey O'Brien Award}}\n{{Johnny Unitas Award}}\n{{Manning Award}}\n{{Southeastern Conference Football Player of the Year navbox}}\n{{NCAA major college football passing yardage leaders}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burrow, Joe}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:All-American college football players]]\n[[Category:American football quarterbacks]]\n[[Category:Heisman Trophy winners]]\n[[Category:LSU Tigers football players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Maxwell Award winners]]\n[[Category:Ohio State Buckeyes football players]]\n[[Category:People from Athens, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Ohio]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Ames, Iowa]]